summary: This document is a chain of custody log from the Federal Bureau of Prisons, detailing the seizure and handling of two computers (items NYM-19-00185 and NYM-19-00184) on August 11, 2019. The evidence was recovered and transferred to the Office of the Inspector General (OIG).

events.title: Seizure of computers from Federal Bureau of Prisons
events.description: Two computers (item numbers NYM-19-00185 and NYM-19-00184) were seized and placed into evidence custody. The chain of custody log was initiated, and the evidence was designated for transfer to the Office of the Inspector General.

keyFacts: Two computers were seized as evidence by the Federal Bureau of Prisons on August 11, 2019.
The evidence items are identified as NYM-19-00185 (Computer 10214207268) and NYM-19-00184 (Computer # 0214207270).
The chain of custody documents show the evidence was transferred to the Office of the Inspector General (OIG).
The document is a standard evidence custody form, indicating procedural handling of seized items.
No suspect is listed (marked as N/A), and the document focuses on the logistics of evidence preservation.
